\f0\fs21\fsmilli10667 \cf3 Television in Latin America continues to be an important medium for the population; politics, history, the market, and especially the culture and its audiences keep television alive. In spite of the fact that millennials enjoy television from a variety of screens, television contents remain as a reference in everybody\uc0\u32 \u769 s audiovisual experiences. With changes in its reception, production, programming, and business models, television \'93exploits\'94, instead of disappearing, amplifying itself into the televisual, keeping itself as a multicultural experience, and as a unique opportunity for its audiences\'92 reinvention of themselves. 
