\f0\fs26\fsmilli13333 Of course, we are in a new era. Television, the cinema, the radio and the press continue to play important roles, even when they are struggling for their coexistence and against domination with new screens, new technologies and, above all, new \'93reasons powers\'94 of communication (Martin-Barbero, 2001). This new era has been labeled as \'93post- television\'94; but the main authors such as Buonanno (2015) differ, when they admit that television makes its way in a new constellation of communications, that is \'96we would say\'96 in the contemporary media and televisual scenario (Press & Williams, 2010). 
\f1\fs24 \

